@node description "Description"

    Pktfile mover for fakepoints and sysoppoints.

    Takes care of moving netmail and echomail packets from your tosser
    outbound directory to your Fido editor inbound directory (And the other
    way around off course :-)). Fileattaches is also handled correctly.

    Pktfiles are moved and renamed with a datestamp. Truncating or deleting
    of files in the flowfile is handled correctly. And there is lots of
    error checking to keep packets from getting lost.

    Optional Storepkt script included. Use it to change a string in the
    pktfile (Eg. change tearlines) and store the pktfile directly in the
    flowfile instead of packing it.

@endnode
@node installation "Installation"

    Just copy the script to rexx: and the config file to mail:

    Caution: If you put the pktshovel.cfg file somewhere else than mail:
    you have to edit the 'cfgfile' variable in the start of the script.

@endnode
@node configuration "Configuration"

    Example cfg file:

    SYSTEM CM
    ;
    MOVE out: in: 2:238/38.0
    MOVE out: in: 39:140/110.0
    ;
    SYSTEM BOTH
    ;
    MOVE out: post:spot_in_max/ 2:238/38.2
    MOVE out: post:spot_in_max/ 39:140/110.2
    MOVE out: post:spot_in_max/ 2:99/999.2
    MOVE out: post:spot_in_louice/ 2:238/38.1
    MOVE out: post:spot_in_louice/ 2:99/999.1
    ;

    A group of MOVE command must come after a SYSTEM command. The syntax of
    the SYSTEM command is:
    SYSTEM <name>
    And the syntax of the MOVE command is:
    MOVE <fromdir> <todir> <what address to move>.

    If you would like to run some command (Eg. an aftersession script)
    after moving the pktfiles you can specify a DOSCOM command for each
    SYSTEM. The syntax is:
    DOSCOM <command>. 
    The command is executed just as if you started it from CLI (It is not
    treated as another Arexx script).

@endnode
@node usage "Usage"

    USAGE
    rx rexx:pktshovel.rexx <SYSTEM>

    System is the name of one of the group of move commands in the @{" config " link configuration}
    file.
    
    You will probably want to insert the Pktshovel command in your
    aftersession script.

@endnode
@node tips "Tips"

    It's a good idea to turn off packing of pktfiles in your tosser and
    Fido editor. After all you're only moving packets around on your
    harddisk so there's no need to spend time packing them.

    If you want to change some text in the packets (Eg. change tearlines)
    without having to pack them have a look at the @{" Storepkt " link storepkt} script.

@endnode
