@node history "History"

    2.0 - Almost a total rewrite of Mat's 1.x versions.
          Fileattaches is now handled 100% correctly.
          So is truncating and deleting of files in the flowfile.
          No longer uses any external commands (Like c:copy).
          Lots of error checks added. Packets can no longer 'get lost'
          because of eg. a missing directory.
          Directory specifications does not have to end in '/' :-) 
          It's a bit faster too.
          Added Storepkt script.
    2.0a - Aargh, a wrong (nonfunctioning) version of Storepkt was included
           in the archive by accident.

@endnode
@node storepkt "Storepkt"

    Storepkt is a script you can install as a packer in your Fido editor.

    It allows you to replace a string in pktfiles with another. After that
    it stores the pktfile in the flowfile without packing it.

    Install it in your Fido editor where you specify which packer a system
    uses. Instead of eg. "lha a" you write "rx rexx:storepkt.rexx"

    Then edit the config section of the script. Change the variable
    'search' to the strings you want changed. And the variable 'replace'
    the string you want it changed to.

@endnode
